\c 34
\p
\v 1 Of David when he pretended to be insane before Abimelech and he drove him out and he went.
\q1
\v 2 I will bless YHWH at all times,
\q1 His praise will continually be in my mouth.
\q1
\v 3 In YHWH my soul boasts,
\q1 Let the poor hear and be glad.
\q1
\v 4 Magnify YHWH with me,
\q1 And let us exalt his name together.
\q1
\v 5 I sought YHWH and he answered me,
\q1 And from all my fears he delivered me.
\q1
\v 6 They looked to him and they shone,
\q1 Do not let their faces be ashamed.
\q1
\v 7 This poor one cried, and YHWH heard,
\q1 And from all his distress he saved him.
\q1
\v 8 The angel of YHWH encamps around those who fear him,
\q1 And he delivers them.
\q1
\v 9 Taste and see that YHWH is good,
\q1 Happy is the man who takes refuge in him.
\q1
\v 10 Fear YHWH, O his holy ones,
\q1 For there is no lack for those who fear him.
\q1
\v 11 Young lions are poor and hungry,
\q1 But those who seek YHWH will not lack any good thing.\f + \ft Cf. Pss 15 and 24.\f*
\q1
\v 12 Come, O children, listen to me,
\q1 I will teach you the fear of YHWH.
\q1
\v 13 What man desires life?
\q1 Loves days to see good?
\q1
\v 14 Keep your tongue from evil,
\q1 And your lips from speaking deceipt.\f + \ft Ps 15:2; 24:4.\f*
\q1
\v 15 Turn aside from evil and do good,
\q1 Seek peace and pursue it.
\q1
\v 16 The eyes of YHWH are to the righteous ones,
\q1 And his ears tthe o their cries for help.\f + \ft For vv. 13-16, cf. Pss 15 and 24.\f*
\q1
\v 17 The face of YHWH is against those who do evil,
\q1 To cut off their memory from earth.
\q1
\v 18 They cry out, and YHWH hears,
\q1 And from all their distress he delivers them.
\q1
\v 19 YHWH is near to the broken hearted,
\q1 And he saves the crushed of spirit.
\q1
\v 20 Many are the troubles of the righteous,
\q1 But from them all YHWH saves him.
\q1
\v 21 He keeps all his bones,
\q1 Not one of them will be broken.
\q1
\v 22 Evil kils the wicked,
\q1 And those who hate the righteous are guilty.\f + Ps 15:4.\f*
\q1
\v 23 YHWH redeems the life of his servants,
\q1 And none of those who take refuge in him will be guilty.